   generation pipelines in theoretical medical knowledge},
Journal = {DATA IN BRIEF},
Year = {2025},
Volume = {63},
Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {The paper introduces RAGCare-QA, an extensive dataset of 420 theoretical
   medical knowledge questions for assessing Retrieval-Augmented Generation
   (RAG) pipelines in medical education and evaluation settings. The
   dataset includes one-choice-only questions from six medical specialties
   (Cardiology, Endocrinology, Gastroenterology, Family Medicine, Oncology,
   and Neurology) with three levels of complexity (Basic, Intermediate, and
   Advanced). Each question is accompanied by the best fit of RAG
   implementation complexity level, such as Basic RAG (315 questions, 75.0
   \%), Multi-vector RAG (82 questions, 19.5 \%), and Graph-enhanced RAG
   (23 questions, 5.5 \%). The questions emphasize theoretical medical
   knowledge on fundamental concepts, pathophysiology, diagnostic criteria,
   and treatment principles important in medical education. The dataset is
   a useful tool for the assessment of RAG-based medical education systems,
   allowing researchers to fine-tune retrieval methods for various
   categories of theoretical medical knowledge questions. (c) 2025 The
