Year = {2026},
Volume = {20},
Number = {3},
Month = {MAR 4},
Abstract = {Despite the availability of pro-business policies, many micro, small and
   medium-sized enterprises (MSMEs) struggle to effectively utilise these
   resources due to limited capacity. This study proposes an
   policy-enterprise matching framework that transforms `enterprises
   seeking policies' approach into a `policies seeking enterprises'
   mechanism. The mechanism uses large language models (LLMs) as tool for
   extracting policy restrictive clauses and generating compliance checking
   strategies. Meanwhile, machine learning methods are used for enterprise
   risk prediction. The matching framework broadens the research
   perspective of policy analysis and risk prediction, and provides
   government staff with decision support based on risk prediction.},
